Build ubuntu-plucky sdcard for Radxa rockpi4b:

Input files: ../rootfs-ubuntu-plucky/linaro-esp.img
             ../rootfs-ubuntu-plucky/linaro-rootfs.img

Plugin NVME-SSD/sdcard/emmc to PC.
sudo ./mksdcardimg.sh
Eject NVME-SSD/sdcard/emmc from PC.

Plugin NVME-SSD/sdcard/emmc to rockpi4b.
Login:
Username: linaro
Password: linaro
Setup wifi. Disable power saving and screen saver.
uname -a
lsb_release -a
sudo ifconfig
sudo dpkg-reconfigure tzdata
sudo dpkg-reconfigure locales
date
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade
sudo apt dist-upgrade
sync
free
glxinfo | grep OpenGL
date
Check if Ubuntu is running UEFI mode:
ls /sys/firmware/efi
Check display mode: ( wayland or x11 )
echo $XDG_SESSION_TYPE
Check audio driver: ( pulseaudio or pipewire )
pactl info

sudo apt install speedtest-cli python3-pip python3-setuptools ffmpeg mpv glmark2-es2-wayland pandoc vlc vlc-plugin-video-output

speedtest-cli --secure

glmark2-es2-wayland

aplay -l
pavucontrol  ( select card 1 as default )

sudo add-apt-repository ppa:mozillateam/ppa
sudo apt update; sudo apt upgrade -y;
sudo apt install firefox-esr
firefox-esr -> youtube.com -> search YmDNhi07_Ho

git clone https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp.git
cd yt-dlp
make
cd ../
\rm -f swan.mp4
~/yt-dlp/yt-dlp -f "bestvideo[ext=mp4][vcodec^=avc1]+bestaudio[ext=m4a]/best" --merge-output-format mp4 --recode-video mp4 3qrKjywjo7Q -o swan.mp4
mpv swan.mp4
ffplay swan.mp4
cvlc --gl=wgl --glconv=any swan.mp4

sudo rfkill list
hciconfig hci0
hcitool dev
hciconfig -a
